parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off while driving
loss of power
unusual noises (e.g.
knocking
grinding
or clunking)
oil leaks
low oil pressure
and warning lights illuminating on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Knocking and Rod Bearing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine rod bearings can cause the engine to seize or fail, leading to accidents or stranding the driver, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine knocking or tapping noise
loss of power
warning lights illuminating on the dashboard
and engine stalling or shutting off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Leaks and Low Oil Pressure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks and low oil pressure can cause engine damage or failure, leading to accidents or stranding the driver, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Oil leaks
low oil pressure
warning lights illuminating on the dashboard
and engine stalling or shutting off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Issues and Lack of Notification
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to notify owners of recalls and provide timely repairs can lead to continued driving of unsafe vehicles, potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Owners not receiving recall notifications
dealerships unable to perform repairs
and vehicles not being repaired in a timely manner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to shake or jerk uncontrollably, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or jerks uncontrollably
the steering wheel makes a loud rattling or clicking noise
the steering wheel feels loose or has excessive play
the vehicle pulls to one side
the traction control warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric power steering pump can cause the loss of power steering, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering warning light illuminates
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to steer
the power steering pump makes a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering coupler can cause the steering wheel to shake or jerk uncontrollably, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or jerks uncontrollably
the steering wheel makes a loud rattling or clicking noise
the steering wheel feels loose or has excessive play.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dim or ineffective headlights can cause reduced visibility while driving at night, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The headlights are dim
the low beam headlights do not illuminate the road
the headlights have a poor light pattern
the headlights are not bright enough
the headlights are only visible to the sides
the headlights are not visible at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty brake lights can cause accidents or near-misses, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop.
symptoms: The brake lights do not work
the brake lights are dim
the brake lights do not turn on when the brake pedal is pressed
the brake lights are only visible when the turn signal is activated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system issues can cause a range of problems, including faulty lighting, reduced vehicle performance, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The interior dome light goes on and off while driving
the electronic stability control light comes on
the turn signal lights fail to work
the tail lights do not work when the brake pedal is pressed.
